seriesStories.title: Bermuda win Americas title
seriesStories.subTitle: World Cricket League Americas Division
seriesStories.summary: Bermuda won the World Cricket League Americas Division 1 Championship for the first time

seriesStories.title: Bermuda bag title after Canada's win
seriesStories.subTitle: World Cricket League Americas Division
seriesStories.seoTitle: Bermuda bag title after Canada's win
seriesStories.summary:
John Davison, the Canadian captain, lead the way to his side's  ten-wicket victory 
over  USA  in Ontario, on Saturday

image.caption: John Davison watches his match-winning stroke go to the boundary to give Canada a 10-wicket win over USA
image.longCaption: John Davison, the Canadian captain, watches his match-winning stroke go to the boundary to give his side a 10-wicket win over USA. Davison made 62 not out, at Maple Leaf Cricket Club, August 26, 2006

seriesStories.title: Rain halts Bermuda's progress
seriesStories.subTitle: World Cricket League Americas Division
seriesStories.summary: Rain and bad light put an end to the  top-of-the table clash  between  Bermuda   and  USA   in Ontario on Friday

image.caption: Sushil Nadkarni cuts during his 83 against Bermuda
image.longCaption: Sushil Nadkarni cuts during his 83 against Bermuda, ICC World Cricket League Americas Division, 7th match, King City, Ontario

seriesStories.title: Consolation win for Canada
seriesStories.subTitle: World Cricket League Americas Division
seriesStories.summary: Canada  won their first game of the tournament, beating  Argentina    by 9 wickets  in a rain interrupted match

seriesStories.title: USA set up Bermuda showdown
seriesStories.subTitle: World Cricket League Americas Division
seriesStories.summary: The United States cruised to a comfortable seven-wicket win over Argentina on the third day of the Americas Championship at Maple Leaf CC in Toronto, Canada, and in doing so set up a potential championship decider with Bermuda on Friday.
